[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering modifications for class resolution**\n\nI'm thinking about whether we should switch to using `resolveClass` instead of descriptor spoofing. It could enhance the supported behavior, but then deserializing a stream as one class while treating it as another feels a bit off for a standard library API. Currently, the manual spoofed descriptor mimics legacy serialized bytes, which has its own reasons for existing. I need to weigh the pros and cons of such a modification carefully.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_085bd9c3cf982890016a25ff8b74d08195911ba8e665771c02\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJf-3YF9aisdmqG6Df_sJgJvLqBTakv5t3CwmcAyti0YJfavLUG3ygQjgQtN9EWcSvpo93psf3t6i3jjX2zCQHizVAqF4q9hGsWm0rqduzlsmP54wwB9IqTfjd45fnqdRBUujYFt_NAoJcep9Y97cyfuY61KOK0CTHKg-kHc1X4rn8CuoImgW4HKRzd2SB-ALkzTj-Bax0Mf0hhNPOomXnhlwQo5W9IcVf2wLv1tl6lMMSop_70RViu5ZPJYuO1NJUzMDAFm9z9QE7RlTpocT2LxI7xc4heYEM_jH5R-rFWYBC98epu7K98GnsSs3djKQadqBcOLRgq3d3cbz_zKBhAyrcsxBYQDdmp9x5CTQkEuR_L8_XY-6OmC0T7o4H6shoHeqyyVJekIriiNRqmn0qBTjbVTgly0DnEVkHjQUhguXoGUavRUyp3ww97hhZbZDTtWMbq3ClWtabweqJFU4kpSTrjQbII9ioO7rLgtfWSIetaluWD5BfmOo6fzhHYfIGp8KZnZMqupoDXt1AUHCYb1v8AJ2-RjzWE5q4miczNVkt9nQ68o68Hn_Y9FuVVq9dhux0RjWyANNYjZptCi0SmMypk7kN_1hofb-EnfqpmXj98z45bmdoeRZ5losPJn3Zxj3tiO_6odB2JJslEFflIKPoKBH6dsDIs4MeSirAy7Via8xkqLnucZc_09iirN5Su1MoHCmpdFREU260YbbDMJb-IHKV0sVEJ9haXPz2aBn7zVZYVy2xun35zBvLVKwWnlb728nPmPJ03yFJh3dyOs_Xm_SwcSCxDm5-LNuLWBReJt_yxDX0Wn1ayre7fFkqYNIrT0kOfqeKv8f9ZJxOHZtcUBhLyldUfOwm6PevzfEWPTC_ZK6DuXHz0EOdX5zziJ8s9qe2-8EXCXCZ-BP34lI_l1ts3iSQVwaeA9mCuxOgZgNzuRD47kR1jaPhGggJGgSf9iEPqBkgl31xNKg57_b2KsMrUV9N2Xr_WxJfu2c57YnmsnFx1SqYEfinZaV2a8oDT32vJoJURrjdPxUxLzlF8fPw6z0_qvd-ec8TWqGCyfY73gwq2I0xNiLD00z5jdCCGlLk3_veuZI8YFbacsmgkVs4VoZx_2AOjuYawtdsw_tViHSwo2ZP3peCQsSpE6sjZkJd1uBmQLwupY7EKEBVmq03_shZD8iKiJt1YKGewJsB_PNFczo798G8SvEpltOe2Olehw0vZFrma_vMl_