n script to create Java serialization accurately. First, I need to understand the binary format, which includes elements like STREAM_MAGIC and version information. The serialized form of BigInteger is key, but it comes with various JDK specifics that complicate things. Instead of hardcoding it, using ObjectOutputStream to create the BigInteger at runtime sounds like a better plan. I could even store the generated byte stream, but I wonder if I should run a small Java snippet for testing. However, I may not need to do that.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering static fixtures for serialization**\\n\\nI'm thinking about using a static fixture with the actual class name since it might help when the native agent meets the JVM. If the ObjectInputStream sees the JCE class, it also sees the descriptor when the stream is written. There doesn’t seem to be a difference. Maybe generating a static fixture can help remove the custom class and avoid descriptor overrides. I could also explore using Base64 for encoding. This approach might simplify the situation a bit!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_9EGKvpReK282S64w3FDLQykO|fc_085bd9c3cf982890016a25ffec8988819592a10fd6c9ba0162", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "cat > /tmp/GenJceElGamalPublicKeyStream.java <<'JAVA'\nimport java.io.*;\nimport java.math.BigInteger;\nimport java.util.Base64;\n\npublic class GenJceElGamalPublicKeyStream {\n  static final String CLASS = \"org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.JCEElGamalPublicKey\";\n  static final long SUID = 8712728417091216948L;\n  static final BigInteger P = BigInteger.valueOf(23L);\n  static final BigInteger G = BigInteger.valueOf(5L);\n  static final BigInteger Y = BigInteger.valueOf(8L);\n  public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {\n    ByteArrayOutputStream byteOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n    try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutputStream = new JCEElGamalPublicKeyObjectOutputStream(byteOutputStream)) {\n      objectOutputStream.writeObject(new SerializedJceElGamalPublicKey());\n    }\n    System.out.println(Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(byteOutputStream.toByteArray()));\n  }\n  static final class SerializedJceElGamalPublicKey implements Serializable {\n    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;\n    private void writeObject(ObjectOutputStream outputStream) throws IOException {\n      outputStream.writeObject(Y);\n      outputStream.writeObject(P);\n      outputStream.writeObject(G);\n    }\n  }\n  static final class JCEElGamalPublicKeyObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n    private static final byte SERIALIZABLE_CLASS_WITH_WRITE_OBJECT = 0x03;\n    JCEElGamalPublicKeyObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream) throws IOException { super(outputStream); }\n    @Override protected void writeClassDescriptor(ObjectStreamClass descriptor) throws IOException {\n      if (SerializedJceElGamalPublicKey.class.getName().equals(descriptor.getName())) {\n        writeUTF(CLASS); writeLong(SUID); writeByte(SERIALIZABLE_CLASS_WITH_WRITE_OBJECT); writeShort(0); return;\n      }\n      super.writeClassDescriptor(descriptor);\n    }\n  }\n}\nJAVA\njavac /tmp/GenJceElGamalPublicKeyStream.java && java -cp /tmp GenJceElGamalPublicKeyStream", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 823, "output": 1705, "cacheRead": 69120, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 71648, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780875213732, "responseId": "resp_085bd9c3cf982890016a25ffceb0a48195a8e2ed4e66e87c7f"}}
